    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Skullcaps worn by ordained officiates in the Catholic Church. The color varies according to rank: white is for the pope, red for cardinals, violet for bishops, and black for all others.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046678/Oxford Dictionary of the Christian Church (1983)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000050867/Catholic Encyclopedia online (1997-2003)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Kalotten die door gewijde officianten in de katholieke kerk worden gedragen. De kleur is afhankelijk van de functie: wit is voor de paus, rood voor kardinalen, violet voor bisschoppen en zwart voor alle anderen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>天主教教堂中，被任命主持宗教儀式者所戴的無邊便帽。顏色依階級而有所不同：教宗戴白帽，樞機主教戴紅帽，主教戴紫帽，其他則戴黑帽。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Copricapi indossati dagli officiati ordinati nella chiesa cattolica. Il colore varia a seconda del grado: il bianco è per il papa, il rosso per i cardinali, la viola per i vescovi, e il nero per tutti gli altri.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Italian</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109543/Italian Term Processing (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Scheitelkappe, die von ordinierten Geistlichen in der katholischen Kirche getragen wird. Die Farbe variiert entsprechend dem Rang: weiß für den Papst, rot für die Kardinäle, violett für die Bischöfe und schwarz für alle anderen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
